                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Our guild went on a raid last night against Arlyxir (Sol Ro mini).  He dropped 2 <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=17213" target="_blank" class="postlink">Hooded Sanguine Mantle</a>.  After thinking it over, I told my guild leader to pass on me for consideration of this item because I am currently working on the Coldain Shawl (4th currently) and I didn't feel it was right that I loot a no-drop like this and having it go to waste.  He told me he appreciated my honesty and passed me a <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=16331" target="_blank" class="postlink">Pauldrons of Witness</a> to hold me over until I finish it.  My previous shoulders were a <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=23232" target="_blank" class="postlink">Mantle of a Maniacal Magus</a>.
<br />

