<br />
Wouldn't the JC Mastery AA make drilling up Jewelcraft cheaper though by being able to sell back your combines?  I thought that by reducing your failure rates, it should reduce the amount of times you don't get to sell back.  Or is this my misconception?</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
You get to sell back your successes no matter what--all JCM would do is lower the number of failed combines.
<br />

<br />
But--you're talking about saving 18 aa's when the worst thing a failure means is 110 pp (105 pp for the platinum bar and ~3 pp for the jade).  Even 1% of the time you'd spend grinding those 18 Aa will cover the money you'd "lose" in just grinding up the skill.
<br />

<br />
I'd be *shocked* if you lost 5k doing it.  Going from o to 250 (granted, back during Velius) *netted* 15k, just selling to the newbies in the Greater Faydark.  Max your INT and keep your CHA over 150.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />-Sage Lellianna LeBeau
