<br />
With that POV, their are many shoulder pieces available to enchanters in high end guilds.  <a href="http://www.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=17998" target="_blank" class="postlink">Flowing Moss Mantle</a>, <a href="http://www.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=20822" target="_blank" class="postlink">Pauldrons of Purity</a>, <a href="http://www.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=22649" target="_blank" class="postlink">Shawl of Eternal Forces</a>, <a href="http://www.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=27016" target="_blank" class="postlink">Mantle of Mending</a> are a few that come to mind quickly (just a quick listing for HIGH END).  For most enchanters not in an Elemental guild, the Coldain Prayer Shawl is one of the best (if not the best) shoulder piece out there.  It's also not all that hard to get.  Prior to level 60 I was able to solo everything I needed to complete the 6th shawl.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />&lt;DIV&gt;
